E%3Cp%3EWe've%20chosen%20five%20Christmas%20traditions%20that%20are%20as%20American%20as%20fireworks%20on%20the%20Fourth%20of%20July%20and%20turkey%20on%20Thanksgiving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESome%20Americans%20hide%20pickle%20ornaments%20in%20Christmas%20trees%2C%20but%20no%20one%20can%20really%20agree%20on%20how%20this%20tradition%20got%20its%20start.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223776%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22pickle%20ornament%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5dfb94ac954bda030826030c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222832%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPickle%20ornaments.%3Cp%3EMatt%20McClain%20for%20the%20Washington%20Post%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20Americans%20have%20a%20pickle%20ornament%20for%20their%20Christmas%20tree.%20Traditionally%2C%20the%20ornament%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20hidden%20somewhere%20on%20the%20tree%2C%20and%20the%20first%20child%20to%20find%20it%20receives%20an%20extra%20present%2C%20but%20it's%20unclear%20where%20this%20tradition%20started.%20One%20website%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whychristmas.com%2Fcustoms%2Fchristmaspickle.shtml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhy%20Christma%3C%2Fa%3Es%2C%20points%20to%20two%20potential%20origin%20stories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20legend%20goes%20that%20two%20boys%20were%20killed%20by%20an%20evil%20innkeeper%2C%20who%20put%20their%20bodies%20in%20a%20pickle%20barrel%2C%20but%20a%20passing%20Saint%20Nicholas%20was%20able%20to%20magically%20revive%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20suggests%20that%20a%20German-born%20soldier%20in%20the%20American%20Civil%20War%20was%20imprisoned%2C%20and%20begged%20for%20one%20last%20pickle%20before%20he%20died.%20A%20guard%20took%20pity%20on%20him%20and%20gave%20him%20a%20pickle%2C%20which%20miraculously%20sustained%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20theory%20posits%20that%20the%20pickle%20ornament%20got%20its%20start%20in%20Germany%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2016%2F12%2F23%2Fworld%2Fwhat-in-the-world%2Fchristmas-germany-weihnachtsgurke-pickle.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20few%20people%20there%20have%20heard%20of%20it.%20It%20is%20more%20likely%20that%20it%20was%20a%20marketing%20stunt%20invented%20by%20those%20importing%20glass%20decorations%20from%20Germany.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPopcorn%20is%20another%20decoration%20seen%20on%20American%20Christmas%20trees.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223456%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22christmas%20tree%20popcorn%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5c094a7b5930f816092ac053%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222592%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMarie%20C%20Fields%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Christmas%20trees%20as%20we%20know%20them%20are%20said%20to%20have%20originated%20in%20Germany%20in%20the%2016th%20century%20and%20brought%20to%20German%20settlements%20in%20Pennsylvania%2C%20the%20popcorn%20garland%20is%20an%20American%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Christmas%20trees%20were%20a%20relatively%20new%20idea%2C%20people%20had%20to%20get%20creative%20with%20their%20d%C3%A9cor.%20Apparently%2C%20recently%20transplanted%20German%20Americans%20favored%20using%20fruits%20and%20nuts%2C%20thus%20turning%20to%20popcorn%2C%20which%20was%20ubiquitous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedailymeal.com%2Fholidays%2Ffun-christmas-food-facts%2Fslide-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Daily%20Meal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20this%20practice%20was%20originally%20meant%20to%20help%20feed%20birds%20during%20harsh%20winters.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20might%20have%20a%20hard%20time%20understanding%20why%20everyone's%20favorite%20movie%20theater%20snack%20would%20appear%20on%20a%20Christmas%20tree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDrinking%20egg%20yolks%20is%20an%20American%20tradition%20that%20people%20from%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20world%20just%20don't%20understand.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221068%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20glass%20of%20eggnog.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5dfb94fc954bda31fa4e9dc8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22801%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEggnog.%3Cp%3ENSC%20Photography%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thespruceeats.com%2Forigins-of-eggnog-760173%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Spruce%20Eats%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20eggnog%20has%20its%20roots%20in%20posset%2C%20a%20punch%20with%20ale%2C%20raw%20eggs%2C%20and%20figs%2C%20served%20warm.%20British%20monks%20drank%20posset%20all%20the%20way%20back%20in%20the%2013th%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20eventually%20crossed%20over%20to%20America%2C%20where%20it%20was%20renamed%20eggnog.%20Its%20first%20known%20use%20dates%20back%20to%201775%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.merriam-webster.com%2Fdictionary%2Feggnog%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMerriam-Webster.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEggnog%20typically%20consists%20of%20egg%20yolks%20beaten%20with%20sugar%2C%20milk%2C%20and%2For%20cream%20and%20your%20choice%20of%20alcohol.%20Rum%2C%20whiskey%2C%20and%20sherry%20are%20all%20acceptable%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-people-drink-eggnog-christmas-2017-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeggnog%3C%2Fa%3E%20might%20not%20seem%20that%20strange%20to%20Americans%20%E2%80%94%20even%20George%20Washington%20had%20his%20own%20recipe%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20a%20hard%20sell%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%2C%20who%20might%20not%20find%20drinking%20eggs%20appetizing%2C%20let%20alone%20when%20mixed%20with%20rum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EGetting%20drunk%20dressed%20as%20Santa%20is%20one%20festivity%20that's%20spread%20to%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20world.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221948%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22santa%20con%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5dfb95f5954bda2cb61b0ec4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221461%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FSeth%20Wenig%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESantaCon's%20roots%20are%20believed%20to%20be%20in%20'70s%20Danish%20performance%20art%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2F2015%2F12%2F22%2F10640590%2Fsantacon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVox%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20it%20eventually%20crossed%20over%20to%20San%20Francisco%20in%20the%20'90s%2C%20as%20a%20protest%20called%20Santarchy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20secret%20society%20called%20the%20San%20Francisco%20Suicide%20Club%20was%20dedicated%20to%20pranking%20the%20city%20and%20generally%20causing%20chaos%20for%20fun.%20One%20of%20their%20events%2C%20Santarchy%2C%20began%20with%20members%20dressing%20as%20Santa%2C%20sneaking%20into%20bars%20and%20parties%2C%20and%20inciting%20mayhem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20it%20became%20a%20giant%20pub%20crawl.%20One%20of%20the%20biggest%20SantaCons%20takes%20place%20in%20New%20York%20City%20every%20year%2C%20and%20has%20been%20advertised%20as%20a%20charity%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsweek.com%2Fsantacon-nyc-2018-when-it-participating-bars-map-what-1244135%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENewsweek%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20NYC%20SantaCon%20raised%20over%20%24400%2C000%20in%20the%20five%20years%20leading%20up%20to%202018%20by%20asking%20participants%20for%20donations.%20The%20money%20goes%20to%20charities%20across%20the%20city%2C%20such%20City%20Harvest%2C%20The%20Secret%20Sandy%20Claus%20Project%2C%20and%20The%20Food%20Bank%20for%20New%20York%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMostly%2C%20though%2C%20it's%20a%20drunken%2C%20debaucherously%20good%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdi